## Rule 32 — Bug validation [CRITICAL]

- Route: **`bug-validator`** / **`.cursor/skills/phoenix-bug-validation/SKILL.md`** / **`.cursor/agents/bug-validator.md`**
- **READ-ONLY** — no code fixes during validation unless user asks **after** validation; no `agents.*` imports
- **Not in scope:** automatic test cases, Playwright, **`energo-ts-run`** (Rules 35–37 / 36 unless user explicitly asks)
- **Env:** **`environment-resolver`** first; empty Jira Environment → AskQuestion (six envs); **`PROCESS BLOCKED`** — no silent `test` default
- **Phoenix align:** **Rule PHOENIX-SWITCH.0**; prod requires `-ConfirmProd` + user ack
- **Evidence:** Confluence (broad discovery **bug-validator only**) + mandatory Swagger refresh + aligned Phoenix code + DB (supporting, same env)
- **SKILL must cover (do not skip read):** diagram bundles under **`Cursor-Project/config/Diagrams/`** when ticket has no diagram; Confluence **Phase 2 exclusion** on Prod/PreProd (prefer Phase 1 wiki); attachment recovery — see **`.cursor/skills/phoenix-bug-validation/SKILL.md`**
- **Slack** `bug-validation` **only when user explicitly asks**; disk report only when user explicitly asks to save (**Rule 0.6**)
- **Rule 41** applies to any EnergoTS `.spec.ts` work — Rule 32 does not author specs

Violation is a **BLOCK**.

