## Rule 35 / 35a — Test case generation [CRITICAL]

When the user requests test cases, run **in order** (gates fixed — **`test_cases_structure.mdc`**):

| Step | Action | Canonical |
|------|--------|-----------|
| **0a** | Ask environment (six envs) if not named | **`environment-resolver`**, TC-ENV-ASK.0 |
| **0b** | Ask Backend vs Backend+Frontend | TC-FRONTEND-ASK.0 |
| **0c** | Align Phoenix (`switch-phoenix-branches.ps1`) | PHOENIX-SWITCH.0 |
| **1** | **cross-dependency-finder** (35a: Jira + code + shallow Confluence; **no** merge/git archaeology) | **`.cursor/skills/cross-dependency-finder/SKILL.md`** |
| **2** | **test-case-generator** with `cross_dependency_data`; read playwright instructions pack + Test Case Template; **TC-STANDALONE-PRE.0** | **`.cursor/skills/test-case-generator/SKILL.md`** |
| **2.5** | **test-case-quality-validator** — 10-axis, **≥80/100**, max **3** rewrites; block if still failing | **`.cursor/skills/test-case-quality-validator/SKILL.md`** |

**Outputs:** `test_cases/Backend/<Topic>.md` always; `test_cases/Frontend/<Topic>.md` only if user chose Backend+Frontend.

**Never skip** Step 1 (cross-dep) or Step 2.5 (quality gate). Violation is a **BLOCK**.

